author: jdonnerstag
msg: Eelco reminded me that loading markup resource streams doesn't work
properly yet if a custom markup cache key is provided. I changed the
code, it should be backportable to 1.3, but the API has slightly
returning MarkupResourceStreamLookupResult, there are now 2 new
Both have just one method. Default implementation exists and are used
by MarkupCache by default, and can be subclassed. If the component
implements any of the two interfaces there respective methods are
called instead of the default ones.
